<p itemprop="description">Version control involves managing changes to code, documents, and other digital assets over time, enabling collaboration, tracking changes, and maintaining historical records of development work.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the importance of version control and recognise common version control concepts and workflows in software development.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can use version control systems effectively, manage branches, commit changes, and collaborate with others using established version control practices.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can establish version control strategies, manage complex branching workflows, and implement version control best practices across development teams.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can design enterprise version control architectures, establish organizational standards, and drive adoption of advanced version control practices across government organizations.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

